=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">The company itself appeared to be on a ste=
ep ascent when,
shortly after Covid hit, NASA announced that it was canceling the use of th=
e Zero-G jet for research purposes=E2=80=94a decision that was going to eli=
minate about 40 percent of Zero-G=E2=80=99s business at that time. =E2=80=
=9CThis was, like, existential,=E2=80=9D Gohd recalled. He furloughed all t=
he employees besides his finance executive, returned the $1.5 million of fu=
nding that was in escrow, and started using his Platinum Amex card to pay Z=
ero-G=E2=80=99s expenses. Meanwhile, he calculated the amount needed to get=
 the company
through the jet=E2=80=99s next scheduled maintenance program in June 2020.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">To make up the shortfall, Gohd decided to pivot =
to an experience business=E2=80=94one poised to benefit from the sort of qu=
irky, devil-may-care spending decisions that wealthier people were making d=
uring the homebound days of the lockdown=E2=80=94particularly as consumer s=
pace travel, from <strong>Richard Branson</strong>=E2=80=99s Virgin Galacti=
c to
<strong>Jeff Bezos</strong>=E2=80=99 Blue Origin and <strong>Elon Musk</str=
ong>=E2=80=99s SpaceX, was becoming a one-percenter bucket-list item. There=
 is even a company, Space Perspective, that offers to take people up to 125=
,000 feet in a luxury hot air balloon for $125,000. At around $10,000 per c=
ustomer, Zero-G was much cheaper=E2=80=94and much less risky=E2=80=94than t=
hose options.=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s not like going up on Bl=
ue Origin for a million and a
half bucks for a 10-minute rocket ride, which would scare the shit out of 9=
0 percent of the population,=E2=80=9D Gohd told me, =E2=80=9Cor going up wi=
th [Branson] on a rocket glider [at $600,000 per flight].=E2=80=9D Plus, =
=E2=80=9COur safety record is impeccable. Nobody=E2=80=99s ever been hurt. =
We=E2=80=99ve flown 22,000 people plus.=E2=80=9D After Gohd proved to the F=
=2EA.A. that the air circulating within=
 his jet was purified and filtered, th=
e agency agreed, during Covid, to let the general public experience brief p=
eriods of weightlessness.=C2=A0</p>
